social_posts.post_text: I feel like I’m doing well

I recently celebrated a birthday. This birthday was totally different for me in many ways. 2022 was a year of ME. I chose ME. I ate alone, cried alone, laughed alone, talked to myself often, vacationed alone, and made the biggest move of my life so far ! Brooklyn, Bexton and I have moved in ! You are our home now, this year is going to be one for the books! 
I am a rare individual, and I KNOW it now❤️

Anyone out there struggling to make that move, go for that dream.. it’s scary but know this. You can do it and know you are worthy of every dream you have 🙌🏼
Don’t look at the caption, look at me 🙌🏼
With all due respect… Sometimes no respect is due -Sza
That’s a wrap on 2022 ! Thank you to my agents and clients for allowing me to do what I love ❤️

I chose inner peace in 2022, I thought about how difficult it would be to choose just for me. Trusting that choosing for me meant the ones around me may question the “new me” but truthfully WE were just getting started knowing the real me.

I went to my girl’s @caseylcohen spin class this am, and a song came on… “f with me, you know I got it” 
I looked right in that mirror and said that to myself “f with me, you know I got it” me talking to me. 
I took self doubt off the table last year, little by little each day my mindset on myself started to change. Life around me started to change, what I considered as my worst fears were actually prayers being answered. 

I see “I feel bad for you, you fumbled me” BUT really I was the one fumbling myself which kept me eating that low hanging fruit. 

Today, my plate is full with all the thick fruits of life. A little change each day, will one day have you looking back seeing they were much bigger than you could see at that time. 

New year, new growth, wiser you ☀️
The change will be worth it…
